SAFA's position remains unchanged. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Football Association was not happy with suggestions of matches being played behind closed doors. READ: PSL suspends all mid-week, weekend games Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa gave the PSL the go-ahead, to look into playing domestic matches behind closed doors. But SAFA has insisted that matches remain suspended due to the threat of COVID-19. SAFA President Dr Danny Jordaan says SAFA's decision is final and binding. South Africa has 116 confirmed coronavirus cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.